cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for automated detection and counting of blood cells in microscopic images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The application of this technology for medical diagnosis also suggests relevance to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of microfluidic point-of-care medical devices implies a potential intersection with the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, as well as the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category due to the use of images and videos for analysis.
